Package Database

Class DatabaseNavigator

java.lang.Object
Database.DatabaseNavigator
public class DatabaseNavigator
extends java.lang.Object
A class that is used by all programs to send the correct response and to receive the response turning it into a string To send data across to the server you must have, in this order: response integer, authentication details (can be empty), and data for the sql query

    static class  DatabaseNavigator.Response
    The list of integers for responses to queries from the control panel or viewer NOTE: This is only used by the viewer and the control panel EXAMPLE OF HOW TO USE: "DatabaseStatements.Response.STORE_BILLBOARD_SCHEDULE.getValue();"

    • DatabaseNavigator

      public DatabaseNavigator​(java.lang.Object[] objects, DatabaseToken auth, java.sql.Connection connection) throws java.lang.Exception
      The constructor for database statements NOTE: This is only used by the server
      Parameters:
      objects - the data received
      auth - the current Hashmap that is storing all the currently active tokens
      connection - the current instance of the database connection
      Throws:
      java.lang.Exception - throws an exception when the token authentication fails meaning the token has expired
